result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Anthony K Singleton in court with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.  Melissa Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State moves to have this case dismissed and read-in to 13CM1247, Court grants the State's motion. Conditions of bail remitted.

Defendant Anthony K Singleton in court with attorney Nicole Masnica for attorney Jorge R Fragoso.  Andrea M. Will appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defense is requesting another date in approximately 45 days. Discovery was just handed over to Atty. Masnica from the State. Court will give a further proceeding in 30 days for both matters - 13CM1247 and 15CM009.  Hearing scheduled for February 17, 2015 at 02:30 pm.

Defendant Anthony K Singleton in court, in custody.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant advises he was supposed to have counsel. Defendant to speak to Public Defender in the jail. Atty. Elizabeth Weathers appears as a friend of the court and advises the defendant to fill out an inmate communication form. Court will give another date in 2 weeks.  Hearing scheduled for January 16, 2015 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Anthony K Singleton in court, in custody.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant allowed a phone call.  NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED BY COURT.
  Hearing scheduled for January 7, 2015 at 10:00 am.
